    <p>{`After the pool we grabbed some lunch, and took a small walk looking for some of the nearby Buddhist temples by our hotel. We didn’t actually find the one we were looking for, but we did find some that looked pretty interesting, and more interestingly, got to explore the area. Most of the streets are quite small, barely a two-way, and often no sidewalk. Nothing is too busy though, and everyone you see doesn’t seem to be in any extreme hurry. (This contrasted with the crowds of people running for the escalators on every MTR stop). It is definitely a nice change of pace.`}</p>
